==English==

===Intransitive verb phrase===
'''ground out''' (''past'', '''grounded out''')

#{{baseball}} To become [[out]] by hitting a [[ground ball]] which is fielded and leads to a force or tag of a runner
#: ''Jones '''grounded out''' to lead off the third.''

===Noun phrase===
'''ground out'''

#{{baseball}} An instance of grounding out
#: ''A '''ground out''' was recorded on the scorecard.''